The paper deals with algorithms for pre-processing sparse matrices, which is a common problem in scientific computing. The focus is on the minimum degree ordering, which is a well-known primitive for reducing fill in Gaussian elimination. This suggests that the paper is likely to be in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), or computational complexity (cs.CC).
